&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Keeps track of all known CacheManagers. \n \n \n  \n protected &nbsp; CacheManagerEventListenerRegistry    \n    cacheManagerEventListenerRegistry   \n\n \n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The listener registry \n \n \n  \n protected &nbsp; Map &lt; String , CacheManagerPeerListener &gt;   \n    cacheManagerPeerListeners   \n\n \n&nbsp;\n--- net/sf/ehcache/config/ConfigurationFactory.html True\n \n \n \n \n \n \n \nConfigurationFactory (Ehcache Core 2.5.0 API)\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \nfunction windowTitle()\n{\n    if (location.href.indexOf('is-external=true') == -1) {\n        parent.document.title=\"ConfigurationFactory (Ehcache Core 2.5.0 API)\";\n    }\n}\n \n \n \n\n \n\n \n \n\n\n \n   \n  \n \n \n \n   \n \n   \n          Overview   &nbsp; \n          Package   &nbsp; \n    &nbsp;  Class  &nbsp; \n          Use   &nbsp; \n          Tree   &nbsp; \n          Deprecated   &nbsp; \n          Index   &nbsp; \n          Help   &nbsp; \n   \n \n \n  \n ehcache  \n \n \n\n \n  \n&nbsp;  PREV CLASS  &nbsp;\n&nbsp;  NEXT CLASS    \n  \n    FRAMES    &nbsp;\n&nbsp;  NO FRAMES    &nbsp;\n&nbsp; \n    All Classes  ');\n  }\n  //-->\n \n \n    All Classes  \n \n\n\n  \n \n \n  \n  SUMMARY:&nbsp;NESTED&nbsp;|&nbsp;FIELD&nbsp;|&nbsp;CONSTR&nbsp;|&nbsp; METHOD   \n  \nDETAIL:&nbsp;FIELD&nbsp;|&nbsp;CONSTR&nbsp;|&nbsp; METHOD   \n \n \n  \n \n\n \n \n \n \nnet.sf.ehcache.config \n \nClass ConfigurationFactory \n \n java.lang.Object \n    net.sf.ehcache.config.ConfigurationFactory \n \n \n \n  public final class  ConfigurationFactory  extends  Object  \n \n\n \nA utility class which configures beans from XML, using reflection.\n \n\n \n \n  Version:  \n   $Id: ConfigurationFactory.java 2675 2010-08-25 09:53:02Z lorban $ \n  Author:  \n   Greg Luck \n \n \n\n \n\n \n\n   \n \n \n  \n Method Summary   \n \n \n  \n static&nbsp; Configuration    \n    parseConfiguration  () \n\n \n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Configures a bean from an XML file in the classpath. \n \n \n  \n static&nbsp; Configuration    \n    parseConfiguration  ( File &nbsp;file) \n\n \n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Configures a bean from an XML file. \n \n \n  \n static&nbsp; Configuration    \n    parseConfiguration  ( InputStream &nbsp;inputStream) \n\n \n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Configures a bean from an XML input stream. \n \n \n  \n static&nbsp; Configuration    \n    parseConfiguration  ( URL &nbsp;url) \n\n \n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb\n--- net/sf/ehcache/transaction/manager/DefaultTransactionManagerLookup.html True\n \n \n \n \n \n \n \nDefaultTransactionManagerLookup (Ehcache Core 2.5.0 API)\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \nfunction windowTitle()\n{\n    if (location.href.indexOf('is-external=true') == -1) {\n        parent.document.title=\"DefaultTransactionManagerLookup (Ehcache Core 2.5.0 API)\";\n    }\n}\n \n \n \n\n \n\n \n \n\n\n \n   \n  \n \n \n \n   \n \n   \n          Overview   &nbsp; \n          Package   &nbsp; \n    &nbsp;  Class  &nbsp; \n          Use   &nbsp; \n          Tree   &nbsp; \n          Deprecated   &nbsp; \n          Index   &nbsp; \n          Help   &nbsp; \n   \n \n \n  \n ehcache  \n \n \n\n \n  \n&nbsp;PREV CLASS&nbsp;\n&nbsp;  NEXT CLASS    \n  \n    FRAMES    &nbsp;\n&nbsp;  NO FRAMES    &nbsp;\n&nbsp; \n    All Classes  ');\n  }\n  //-->\n \n \n    All Classes  \n \n\n\n  \n \n \n  \n  SUMMARY:&nbsp;NESTED&nbsp;|&nbsp;FIELD&nbsp;|&nbsp; CONSTR &nbsp;|&nbsp; METHOD   \n  \nDETAIL:&nbsp;FIELD&nbsp;|&nbsp; CONSTR &nbsp;|&nbsp; METHOD   \n \n \n  \n \n\n \n \n \n \nnet.sf.ehcache.transaction.manager \n \nClass DefaultTransactionManagerLookup \n \n java.lang.Object \n    net.sf.ehcache.transaction.manager.DefaultTransactionManagerLookup \n \n \n  All Implemented Interfaces:    TransactionManagerLookup  \n \n \n  Direct Known Subclasses:    EhcacheJtaTransactionManagerLookup  \n \n \n \n  public class  DefaultTransactionManagerLookup  extends  Object  implements  TransactionManagerLookup  \n \n\n \nDefault   TransactionManagerLookup   implementation, that will be used by an   initializing  \n Cache should the user have not specified otherwise.\n  \n This implementation will:\n  \n  try lookup an   InitialContext  ;\n  if successful, lookup a TransactionManager under java:/TransactionManager, this location can be overridden;\n  if it failed, or couldn't find   TransactionManager   instance, look for a Bitronix TransactionManager;\n  and finally an Atomikos one.\n  \n\n To specify under what specific name the TransactionManager is to be found, you can provide a jndiName property using\n   setProperties(java.util.Properties)  . That can be set in the CacheManager's configuration file\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1782774621498}}
